Optional REST parameters should have an object type
Spring provides two options to mark a REST parameter as optional: Use required = false in the @PathVariable or @RequestParam annotation of the respective method parameter or Use type java.util.Optional<T> for the method parameter When using 1., the absence of the parameter, when the REST function is called, is encoded by null, which can only be used for object types. If required = false is used for a parameter with a primitive and the REST function is called without the parameter, a runtime exception occurs because the Spring data mapper cannot map the null value to the parameter.